  <title translate="true">Issue Management (Collaboration)</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Issue Management (Collaboration)</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading 2"><text styleclass="Heading 2" translate="true">Issue LifeCycle</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Issue is created:</text></li>
      <list id="1" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
        <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">created in Revisto (or Revizto plugin in the source software) and assigned to a team member. Issue status is </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">Open</text><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">.</text></li>
        <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Imported as a clash from Navisworks</text></li>
      </list>
    </list>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullet_1" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">The assignee receives an email notification (if configured). The issue automatically becomes available to the assignee in Revizto.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">Optionally, relevant team members can be assigned as issue watchers. Issue becomes available to them for feedback and comments.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">The assignee changes issue status to In progress and starts working on it. If needed, an open issue can be reassigned to another team member.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">When the issue is considered resolved it status is changed to </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">Resolved</text><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Bullet_1"><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">The issue creator reviews the issue and closes it or changes its status back to </text><text styleclass="GUI_item" translate="true">In Progress</text><text styleclass="Bullet_1" translate="true">. Note that a closed issue can be reopened.</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Heading 2"><text styleclass="Heading 2" translate="true">Reporting an Issue and Defining its Settings</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">From Revisto</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="margin-top:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; tabstops:none;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">From a Plugin</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">Issue Settings</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Public/hidden</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Etc.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 2"><text styleclass="Heading 2" translate="true">Clash Management</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 2"><text styleclass="Heading 2" translate="true">Reviewing an Issue and Commenting on it</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">In Revisto</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">In Viewers</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading 3"><text styleclass="Heading 3" translate="true">Via Plugin</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Note"><text styleclass="Note" style="font-weight:bold;" translate="true">Tip</text><text styleclass="Note" translate="true">: When you view issues in Revizto, keep the source software (Revit, Navisworks, etc.) open with the Issue Tracker plugin button pressed. Then, by selecting an issue in Revizto you will be able to see the relevant part of the structure both in Revizto model and in the source software. Note that you can have only one instance of source software simultaneously linked to Revizto. &#160;</text></para>
